"Stop": [
  {
    "hooks": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "command": "[ -n \"$CC_TASKLINE\" ] && exit 0; sleep 0.5 && powershell.exe -Command \"(New-Object Media.SoundPlayer 'C:\\Windows\\Media\\chimes.wav').PlaySync()\""
      }
    ]
  }
],
"Notification": [
  {
    "hooks": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "command": "[ -n \"$CC_TASKLINE\" ] && exit 0; powershell.exe -Command \"(New-Object Media.SoundPlayer 'C:\\Windows\\Media\\chimes.wav').PlaySync()\""
      }
    ]
  }
]

The CC_TASKLINE guard keeps the chime silent inside the nested `claude -p`
haiku calls made by the statusline task-row hook (the guard var is exported
by statusline-task-summary.sh; see Hooks/statusline_task_row). Behavior is
unchanged when CC_TASKLINE is unset.
